500 g Ground Pork
¼ cup Italian Breadcrumbs
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Baby Tomatoes
113 g Baby Spinach
½ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Lemon-Pepper Seasoning
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 unit(s) Lemon
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.  Finely chop half the spinach. Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add chopped spinach to the dry pan. Cook, stirring often, until wilted. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to cool slightly.

While spinach cools slightly, core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices. Halve tomatoes. Zest, then juice half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 ppl). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges. Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Add breadcrumbs, cooked spinach, Lemon-Pepper Seasoning, lemon zest, garlic, half the feta and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt to a medium bowl. Add pork, then combine. (TIP: If you prefer firmer patties, add an egg [2 eggs for 4 ppl] to mixture!) Form mixture into sixteen 2-inch-wide patties (32 patties for 4 ppl).

Reheat the same pan (from step 1) over medium. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then patties. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, cook patties in 2 batches, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.) Pan-fry until cooked through, 3-4 min per side.** Transfer to a plate, then cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, add lemon juice and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. Add tomatoes, peppers, remaining feta and remaining spinach, then toss to combine.

Divide pork patties and lemony tomato-pepper salad between plates.Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.